Frequently Asked Questions

When does the MLB regular season start?

The MLB regular season technically begins on March 18 with a two-game series between the Chicago Cubs and Los Angeles Dodgers in Tokyo. However, for most teams, Opening Day is March 27.

When does the MLB regular season end?

The final day of the MLB regular season is September 28.

How many regular season games in MLB?

Each team plays 162 games in the MLB regular season, for a total of 2,430 games.

What day is Opening Day for baseball in 2025?

Opening Day is March 27.

How long is the MLB regular season?

Each team plays 162 games in the MLB regular season, for a total of 2,430 games.

Why is baseball 162 games?

The MLB schedule expanded to 162 games in 1962, in order to accommodate the league's expansion
